OL,6,FHis barrister told the court that
OL,7,FHarper would lose his security job if
OL,8,Fjailed and would be unable to make his
OL,9,Fmortgage payments. His parents, who he
OL,10,Finformally cared for, would "not be
OL,11,Fable to cope" and his son would have
OL,12,Fto give up his university studies.
OL,14,FJudge Potter told Harper: "I am sure
OL,15,Fyou became obsessed to the point of
OL,16,Fcriminality in stalking Stephanie
OL,17,FGlynn to provide evidence of her
OL,18,Faffair to weaponise that against her
OL,19,Ffor having that affair, and you also
OL,20,Fbecame determined to destroy the
OL,21,Fcareer of Andrew McLullich.
