OL,6,F"In that obsession the feelings,
OL,7,Fembarrassment and pain felt by
OL,8,FStephanie Glynn were collateral
OL,9,Fdamage. You were more concerned about
OL,10,Fyour own feelings and a raging sense
OL,11,Fof injustice."
OL,13,FHe said the events at Screwfix "do no
OL,14,Fcredit to any of the people involved"
OL,15,Fand the incident was "rash, foolish,
OL,16,Fselfish and unprofessional".
OL,18,FJudge Potter went on: "I am sure it
OL,19,Fhas haunted them (Ms Glynn and Mr
OL,20,FMcLullich) and will continue to haunt
OL,21,Fthem for many years."
